data.description:
Tired of scratching up your cookware during storage?

Simply place trivets between your pots and pans when you put them away!

data.title: How to Quickly Chill Wine or Champagne
data.description:
In today's OXO Good Tips video, we show how to quickly chill a bottle of wine or champagne.

Simply place your bottle into an ice bucket then add ice, salt and cold water. Wait for about 10 minutes for the salty ice water mixture chill the bottle. Cheers to never serving a warm glass of wine again!

data.title: How to Remove Mineral Deposits from Stainless Steel Cookware
data.description:
Does your stainless steel cookware look dull from all the mineral deposits that have accumulated over time?

There is no need for harsh chemicals! Just dab a kitchen towel and wipe your pan down with white vinegar to restore your stainless steel pots and pans back to their original luster.
